\q1
\v 11 How shall we magnify Zerubbabel?
\q1 And he was as a signet on the right hand:
\q1
\v 12 So was Jesus the son of Josedek:
\q1 Who in their days built the house,
\q1 And exalted a \f + \fr 49:12 \ft Some ancient authorities read \fqa temple. \f* people holy to the Lord,
\q1 Prepared for everlasting glory.
\q1
\v 13 Also of Nehemiah the memorial is great;
\q1 Who raised up for us the walls that were fallen,
\q1 And set up the gates and bars,
\q1 And raised up our homes again.
\b
\q1
\v 14 No man was created upon the earth such as was Enoch;
\q1 For he was taken up from the earth.
\q1
\v 15 Neither was there a man born like to Joseph,
\q1 A governor of his kindred, a stay of the people:
\q1 Yes, his bones were visited.
\q1
\v 16 Shem and Seth were glorified among men;
\q1 And above every living thing in the creation is Adam.
